OL,3,CJersey's living wage to increase in
OL,4,C2025
OL,6,FCaritas CEO, Patrick Lynch, said: "The
OL,7,Fnew rate was agreed at a meeting of
OL,8,Fthe Jersey Living Wage Advisory Group
OL,9,Fearlier this week.
OL,11,F"This will be good news for many at
OL,12,Faccredited organisations and their
OL,13,Fsubcontractors ahead of the new year
OL,14,Fwhen many will have increased rental
OL,15,Fcosts and also face increases in the
OL,16,Fcost of their utilities".
OL,18,FEarlier in the year, it was agreed
OL,19,Fthat the island's minimum wage would
OL,20,Fincrease to #13 per hour from April
OL,21,F2025.
